                                   \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eAutofill is a lifesaver—until it’s not. Microsoft Authenticator will soon stop saving your passwords, meaning it\u0026#39;s time to switch to Edge or move on to better alternatives.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"say-goodbye-to-password-autofill-in-microsoft-authenticator\"\u003e\n                        Say Goodbye to Password Autofill in Microsoft Authenticator\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you use Microsoft\u0026#39;s Authenticator to autofill passwords on your phone, you\u0026#39;ll soon see a warning to export your passwords and move to Microsoft Edge or other password managers by July 2025, if you haven\u0026#39;t already. The feature will be removed from Authenticator by August 2025.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                    